        "comment": {
            "comments": [
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13470384/comment/17564065",
                    "id": "17564065",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kou",
                        "name": "kou",
                        "key": "kou",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=kou&avatarId=30762",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=kou&avatarId=30762",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=kou&avatarId=30762",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=kou&avatarId=30762"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Kouhei Sutou",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Asia/Tokyo"
                    },
                    "body": "I consider this and here are my opinions:\r\n\r\n* We should use CMake for building share libraries ({{.so}}, {{.dylib}} and {{.dll}}) for JNI\r\n* We should remove all JNI related codes from {{cpp/}}\r\n* We should add {{java/CMakeLists.txt}} to build all shared libraries for JNI\r\n\r\nHere are reasons of my opinions.\r\n\r\n* Maven's shared library building support is too poor (Note that I'm not familiar with Maven. So this may be wrong.)\r\n** -> Maintaining Maven configurations will be higher cost than maintaining CMake configurations\r\n** It seems that we need to use Native Maven Plugin: https://www.mojohaus.org/maven-native/native-maven-plugin/\r\n** Native Maven Plugin doesn't have a feature to choose shared object type for the current environment (e.g. {{.so}} for Linux)\r\n*** We need to prepare one {{pom.xml}} per one shared object type (We need to create {{java/c/c-jni-so}}, {{java/c/c-jni-dylib}} and {{java/c/c-jni-dll}})\r\n** Native Maven Plugin doesn't have a feature to find a library in the current environment\r\n**** We can't detect installed Apache Arrow C++\r\n* We can't build {{.jar}} that works on all environments (Linux, macOS and Windows) on one machine\r\n** We keep using CI to build JNI related artifacts by {{dev/tasks/java-jars/}}\r\n** -> Normal Java developers don't need to think about JNI and CMake. Java developers who work on JNI too need to know CMake but it will not too hard because they know C++.\r\n** We need to build {{.so}}, {{.dylib}} and {{.dll}} for {{.jar}} that works on all environments\r\n** If we build all shared libraries for JNI on one machine, we need to do cross-compiling\r\n** Cross-compiling is very complex. We should avoid it as much as possible.\r\n* We can simplify {{ci/scripts/java_jni_*}} used by {{dev/tasks/java-jars/}} by introducing {{java/CMakeLists.txt}}\r\n** -> We can use general {{cmake ... && cmake --build ... install}} steps to build and install shared libraries for JNI\r\n\r\nI can provide a PoC implementation of this idea if you need.\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=kou",
                        "name": "kou",
                        "key": "kou",
                        "avatarUrls": {
